snippet.title: Dallas cop who shot Botham Jean in his own home charged with murder.
snippet.description:
Former Dallas police officer Amber Guyger was charged with the murder of her neighbor, Botham Jean.  According to Guyger, she accidentally walked into the wrong apartment, saw Jean, and opened fire.  Jean was in his own apartment at the time of the murder. The DA says there is more to the story, and that Guyger is guilty of first-degree murder. In this case, Guyger was White, and Jean was Black. Whether racism played a role in this case remains to be determined, but too many cops are trigger happy, especially when it comes to Black citizens.

Links:
https://dfw.cbslocal.com/2018/11/30/sources-former-dallas-police-officer-amber-guyger-indicted-for-murder/

*****Correction: In the video, I called the shooting victim Jean Botham, which is incorrect. His name was Botham Jean. My apologies.
